data.title: University of Illinois Chicago
data.meta_description: Discover diverse dining options at UIC's SCE. Enjoy a variety of cuisines and convenient meal choices at Student Center East.
data.text:
605 Commons Dining Hall Heading link

605 Commons Dining Hall brings together a great variety of cuisines for you to try out. Explore, Taste, and Discover many flavorful dishes from around the world.

Designed to meet the nutritional needs and the environmental expectations of University students, faculty, staff and visitors.

Today’s Menu

Please note 605 Commons Dining Hall is a cashless location (credit, debit, meal plan or flames fare only)

*Delivery option only for campus housing residents that are under isolation/self-quarantine requirements

Sushi Do, SCE Heading link

Located on 2nd Floor, Inner Circle at Student Center East.

Sushi Do is a contemporary sushi restaurant offering a diverse selection of high-quality, freshly prepared sushi and Japanese cuisine. With a focus on exceptional service and a modern dining atmosphere, the restaurant caters to both traditional and innovative tastes. Its commitment to sourcing premium ingredients and maintaining high standards ensures a memorable dining experience for all guests.

Please note, Sushi Do is a cashless location (credit, debit, or flames fare only)

Coming soon!

Keep up with our website for updates.

Visit our Hours of Operations page for all your favorite location’s holiday hours.

The Halal Shack, SCE Heading link

Located on 2nd Floor, Inner Circle at Student Center East.

Halal Shack offers a range of flavorful, halal-certified dishes, specializing in Mediterranean and Middle Eastern cuisine. Known for its commitment to quality and authenticity, the restaurant caters to diverse dietary preferences with fresh, responsibly sourced ingredients. Its welcoming atmosphere and delicious offerings make it a popular choice for those seeking tasty and compliant meals.

Dunkin’ Donuts Heading link

Dunkin’ Donuts is the world’s leading baked goods and coffee chain, serving more than 3 million customers each and every day. True to our name, we offer 50 varieties of donuts, but you can also enjoy dozens of premium beverages, bagels, breakfast sandwiches and other baked goods. Baskin-Robbins is the world’s largest chain of ice cream specialty shops, providing guests with a wide array of ice cream flavors and delicious treats.

Please note Dunkin’ Donuts is a cashless location (credit and debit only)

Moe's Southwest Grill Heading link

Moe’s offers various types of food on its menu. Burritos, tacos, quesadillas, nachos, salads, stacks, burrito bowls, and salsas with more than twenty ingredients are available to customers to create their own unique meal. These entrees have specific ingredients within it, but ingredients can be added or subtracted from it as the customer customizes their entree. Every order comes with chips and salsa on the side.

Please note Moe’s is a cashless location (credit and debit only)
